@node introduction "x-files - introduction"

                              introduction

ok, you have survived the first issue of x-files and so you had to get
the second issue, because you want to stay informed... :-)

the response was not as big as i have hoped, but for a first issue it
was not bad.

there are some changes in this issue:

 - if you go to the group-selection via first-letter, then :

   - if there are information about groups, the letter is marked with
     a  @{b}.@{ub}  on every side of the gadged.

     it will look like this :       .@{"  E  " link e}. 


   - if there are @{b}new@{ub} information about groups, the letter is marked
     with a  @{b}:@{ub}  on both sides of the gadged.

     it will look like this :       :@{"  E  " link e}:


   - if you have selected a sub-page via a first-letter, there you can
     also see which group has @{b}new@{ub} information to present.
     if there are changes or new information about one of the groups in
     the list, you can see this by the  @{b}:@{ub}  on both sides of the
     gadget.

     it will look like this :       :@{" ethic " link "ethic"}:


   if you want to now if there are information about some groups, you don't
   have to look under every single letter now. look for the .'s and the :'s
   and you will know if there are changed news or if there is everything
   unchanged.


 - now you can use your own font to look at the x-files. it was only a test,
   that i have defined the topaz.font. i forgot to take it out of the
   ready-to-release version

 - small "secret" part included... try to find it. it's not real hidden,
   but it's funny !!!

ok, these are the changes for this issue. if you have some ideas to make
x-files more comfortable for you, then send me your ideas and i will tra to
build them in.

you can also send me a message to tell me if you like or hate the x-files,
or if you only want to talk with me about anything. :-)


now a request from me to :

if you are an ascii-artist, please make me an x-files (only small letters if
possible) logo and send it to one of my addresses or search for me in some
boards, mostly in berlin / germany...


ok, thanx for now and see ya soon...


                                big-rat

@endnode

